LAGOS – Air Peace has re-launched direct flights from the Murtala Muhammed International Airport (MMIA), Lagos and the Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport (NAIA), Abuja to Dubai, the United Arab Emirates (UAE) at the promo fare of N325,000 for a return economy flight. This is as the airline introduced twice-a-week Abuja-Joburg-Abuja connection as well as once-a-week Abuja-Dubai-Abuja flights. Stanley Olisa, the Spokesman of Air Peace stated this on Thursday in a statement. He said: “Passengers in Abuja can now fly Air Peace directly to Dubai and Johannesburg. We have also introduced an amazing promo fare of N325,000 for a return economy flight to Dubai. The promo elapses on May 31, 2022, and Dubai travellers are encouraged to take advantage of this offer.” Olisa maintained that Air Peace would continue to expand its route networks strategically, adding more connections would be introduced, while the airline was consistently modernising its fleet to ease the burden of travel for Africans. He added that Malabo, Equatorial Guinea, is next on the airline’s radar. Air Peace operates into 20 domestic routes, seven regional markets and two international destinations, while it operates an increasing modern fleet of 35 aircraft, including five brand new E195-E2s and five Airbus 320s.